body:
Hi everyone,

I've been seen this error as well. I tried using the Cache-Control headers to expire the cache life but that didn't work at all. In the end, I cancelled the RPC upon any error coming back:

`__block GRPCProtoCall *rpc;
  CompletionBlock connectionErrorCallback =
      ^(id _Nullable response, NSError * _Nullable error) {
        if (error) {
          [rpc cancel];
        }
        responseHandler(response, error);
      };
  // Generate and start the RPC call.
  rpc = [self.myService RPCWithRequest:request handler:connectionErrorCallback];
  [self startRPC:rpc];`

Hope this helps.
Thanks,
